description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM/SECONDMENT FOR 9 MONTHS DUE TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN APPLYING FOR THE SECONDMENT POSITION, YOU MUST OBTAIN PERMISSION FROM YOUR CURRENT LINE MANAGER PRIOR TO APPLYING FOR THIS POST. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note for Welsh students, you must apply via Streamlining where all available jobs can be located. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;This is a new and exciting opportunity for a registered nurse wishing to move into the field of primary care practice nursing in the East area. Opportunities to develop and learn within the environment of general practice will provide the nurse with the skills, competencies and knowledge to become a practice nurse and work effectively and safely in this setting.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post is a fixed 9 month or secondment position which entails being part of a busy GP practice within the East Area working as part of the practice team . The programme will provide a clinical placement with a local GP surgery and offer education and supervision through attending the accredited practice nurse course at University. You will be supported by experienced practice nurse mentors to encourage primary care knowledge, learning and development.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will need to demonstrate their commitment to primary care nursing, the ability to undertake this flexible learning programme and be able to offer a high standard of evidence based practice. Following on from this clinical learning placement, it is anticipated that the newly trained practice nurse will be able to seek practice nurse employment within a north Wales General Practice. Support and assistance will be provided at this time. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Closing Date: 12/11/2020 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Shelley Lewis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Practice Development Nurse Primary Care East Area&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: shelley.lewis2@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07557 009481 &lt;/p&gt;
